7. Conclusion
Building "True JULES" requires the architect to transcend the role of a software engineer and assume the mantle of a control theorist. The architecture is not defined by lines of code but by the mathematical guarantees it enforces. By integrating Stochastic Estimation to build a robust Belief State, Control Theory to enforce a Physics Conscience, and Decision Theory to manage Authority Collapse, JULES realizes the vision of a robotic system that is innately aware of its own limitations. The machine does not just follow orders; it follows the math. This syllabus provides the roadmap for constructing that reality.
